        You may use the site for personal, non-commercial purposes: to look up OBD-II codes, read explanations, and share links to our pages. You may not use the site to distribute malware, attempt to gain unauthorised access to our systems or third-party systems, scrape or harvest content in bulk without permission, or use the site in any way that violates applicable laws or the rights of others.
      </p>
      <p>
        You may not copy large portions of our content and republish it as your own, or use it for commercial products (e.g. paid apps or books) without prior written permission. Short quotations with clear attribution and a link back to our site are acceptable for editorial or educational use.
      </p>

      <h2 id="disclaimer">4. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The site and all content are provided “as is” and “as available”. We disclaim all warranties, express or implied, including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful components. Use of the site and reliance on any information is at your sole risk.
      </p>

      <h2 id="limitation">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, OBD Fault Codes and its operators shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of or inability to use the site, or from any content, errors, or omissions. This includes but is not limited to damages for vehicle repair decisions, lost time, or business interruption. In no event shall our total liability exceed the amount you paid to use the site (if any), or one hundred US dollars, whichever is less.
      </p>

      <h2 id="third-party">6. Third-Party Links and Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        The site may contain links to third-party websites (e.g. tools, manufacturers, or advertising partners). We are not responsible for the content, privacy practices, or availability of those sites. If we display advertising (e.g. through Google AdSense), those ads are provided by third parties and their placement does not constitute an endorsement. Your use of third-party services is subject to their own terms and policies.
      </p>

